## Using the KB

The knowledge base lives in `kb/`. Search it when the user asks about decisions, reasoning, design rationale, or project knowledge.

```bash
# Find notes by description
rg "^description:" kb/notes/ --glob "*.md"

# Find notes by type
rg "^type: note" kb/notes/ --glob "*.md"

# Find notes by tag
rg "^tags:.*my-tag" kb/notes/ --glob "*.md"
```

Key entry points:

- `kb/notes/index.md` — auto-generated directory listing (rebuild with `scripts/generate_notes_index.py`)

